<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> - When a player becomes invisible (or hides successfully) every other player that had them targeted will lose their target. This is true for all servers, but has the greatest implications on PvP servers. The use of spells that allow you to see through invisibility will prevent you from losing your target if that target hides or goes invisible.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p><img src="http://benaan.homestead.com/files/benaan.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulegnavalsharess.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legna ValSharess</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/01 6:23:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nice PvP Change for Rogues</span><hr size=1> Hmm..<br>
<br>
Actually, the way that is worded, we are screwed. A caster will always have see invis up, so hide is still useless.<br>
<br>
However, a caster can cast invis and be gone from us until they begin casting their next nuke. Not surprisingly, once again this is a huge boost for casters, and another gash in the tummy for us. wtg verant, things were not quite unbalanced enough yet.<br>
<br>
-L <p>Legna
55 Shadows
Rallos Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoyoteblack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coyoteblack</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/01 7:28:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nice PvP Change for Rogues</span><hr size=1>         The way I read it is we will be taken off there target list. Bank killing wont be as easy, targeting through walls will be no existent. <br>
<br>
   Also blind poison just became much more powerful. Although I am not questioning your great knowledge in pvp just a thought from a humble backstabbing rogue. <p>" No matter how subtle the wizard, a knife between the shoulder blades will seriously cramp his style"  -- Vlad Taltos</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uslinkerdread.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SlinkerDread</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/01 7:31:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nice PvP Change for Rogues</span><hr size=1> Your assuming that even with see invis up, blind will remove the player off the target list, i bet it doesn't. Since Casters will have see invis up always, this benefit of hide removing off target list, is pretty much pointless as you'l be  removing yourself off the tanks targeting list, meanwhile the wizard will never lose you off target. WHUPS forgot to mention that kendrick <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
hehe sorry no hard feelings just waited for this thing to be coded for 2 years and now see invis is once again going to  ruin this as well as  normal hide. (which should if your motionless keep you hiden even if see invis is up)<br>
<br>
<br>
Slinker <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uplepplop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Plep Plop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/01 8:17:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> I pee'd myself when I saw that message.<br>
<br>
Right... casters have see invis. But seriously, against melees this is incredible. Especially for people who aren't 30+.. Plenty of people still don't see invis pre-30. Only thing that makes me kinda upset is that caster theory...<br>
caster invises and gets ready for his next nuke. Not happy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulegnavalsharess.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legna ValSharess</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/01 11:45:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> They wont fix melee range, but they will stack every possible advantage in favor of the caster. Wow.<br>
<br>
Well, my 53 warrior friend quit just from reading the patch message. Guess chasing ghosts for years and now knowing that casters can abuse them even more now has kind of like crushed their hopes and dreams.<br>
<br>
Can't wait until the next episode of lets screw the melee characters and make sure that only casters will ever be good at pvp.<br>
<br>
-L <p>Legna
55 Shadows
Rallos Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvoodoospirit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>voodoospirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/01 11:45:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hum</span><hr size=1> i know many melees that wear perma see invisible items or bracer of hidden<br>
ie collar of madjj ( whatever it is spelled)<br>
and don t forget our little RS mask  no rogue , treehugger, inky will hide from us ;p<br>
<br>
for the caster guys if they dont jump u first  don t forget a massive pumice dispell  that s always good, with some hope see inv will be at the top , with some luck....<br>
well  steel wand is better but well we got a tiny way to escape from noobie casters now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulegnavalsharess.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legna ValSharess</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/01 5:34:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hum</span><hr size=1> Yes, WE do. But other melee classes are getting wildly screwed by this deal. I really cannot believe that they would impliment something like this and still not even fix the melee range issue, which is the leading cause of caster escapes to date. <br>
<br>
Only fix balance if it benefits the casters, otherwise, &quot;there is nothing that can possibly be done to correct the situation&quot; (ie: Melee binding)<br>
<br>
-L<br>
 <p>Legna
55 Shadows
Rallos Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/01 6:30:25 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hum</span><hr size=1> Melee range is seriously messed up.  Without snare, and even with, everyone can get away.  Is it so hard to change?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugsam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gsam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/01 9:03:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hum</span><hr size=1> I dont think melee range is screwed up at all. Its all about picking your battlegrounds. <br>
<br>
IE: tanks cant PVP for crap in burning woods<br>
<br>
but tanks will kick the @#%$ out of casters in sebilis.<br>
<br>
If you get jumped by a caster in DL and they are ghosting off hills and levitating chase them and then break off and head for a diffrent area if they wanna fight you make them come fight you where you want to fight at. Dont allow them to pick your battleground.<br>
<br>
I play both and know both sides of the issue. I really dont see a problem cept for line of sight which they said will never be fixed.<br>
<br>
Gsam <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/29/01 6:08:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nice PvP Change for Rogues</span><hr size=1> Maybe you don't play a melee Gsam the problem is that if I am running just as fast as someone and get in melee range i can't swing at them I just get the &quot;you are too far away&quot; msg. In other words a caster can run around for a very long time with me right on top of them until I eventually lose track of them possibly through the use of another problem ghosting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uiendyar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iendyar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/29/01 7:38:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> But think about it</span><hr size=1> Say a caster begins to cast a hard hitting nuke, you hit hide and they lose you as a target, they cant retarget you even with see invis on untill the spell is finished being casted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvividardepericulo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vividar DePericulo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/30/01 4:46:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Uhhh</span><hr size=1> Iendyar, you dont seem to understand. If somebody with see invis has you targeted, and you hide IT DOES NOT REMOVE YOU FROM THEIR TARGET. And even if a caster doesnt have see invis on and you hide mid cast, the spell will still hit you. For example when im using my mrylokar vambraces to str buff, i target myself, click, midcast type /target &lt;player name&gt; and when the first cast is finished i click again. You only have to have a person targeted at the beginning of your cast for it to hit/affect them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaximilean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maximilean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/01 4:05:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmmm</span><hr size=1> It is no good versus see-invis, which is too bad.  But obviously making hide work against see-invis would be pretty overpowering. <br>
<br>
This is a nice, if minor adjustment.  As for casters getting as much use out of it as rogues, that's kind of dumb imo.  The only insta-invis a normal caster is going to have is racial hide, that doesn't work half the time.  Or are they going to sit there casting a nice 3 second invis between nukes as some kind of clever trick?<br>
<br>
This will help casters escape, that's true, and theoretically a caster could invis and a melee would have no way of stopping them from sitting down, medding, and resuming the fight.  But in all honesty, the caster could just inter-zone gate half the time anyway.<br>
<br>
And for another thing, there are plenty of pvp spell line-ups that don't include invisibility; it often isn't neccesary, especially if you have shadowstep and gate memmed as your escape spells.  And plenty of (sloppy) casters don't keep see-invis up.  I do, certainly, but plenty don't.  I doubt that holds at high level.<br>
<br>
<br>
So, in closing, perhaps not earth-shattering as it looks, but it's still a rogue buff, since they have the fastest and most reliable invis.<br>
<br>
You can argue that it's no good against a strong caster, but this essentially renders rogues totally invincible against unbuffed melees.  Casters, on the other hand, gain little advantage at all from it.  A lucky escape now and then, but only from a sloppy caster or a melee that could be gated away from just as easily.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/01 4:49:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Any melee who says there's no problem with melee range hasn't played a melee long enough.<br>
<br>
Sure, it's always best to choose your own battleground, but you shouldn't be hindered by a ridiculous "out of range" message while you're riding piggyback on your enemy.  I have a DSL connection and still get this message waaaay too often for my tastes.  <br>
<br>
It's a huge disadvantage against an opponent who can just target me and then attack me from a distance with impunity.  <br>
<br>
Morvran McGuinness <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15>The Arena</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
